# Findings addressed: FIND-409 (deterministic ordering test), FIND-410 (DOM-mount constraint)

## FIND-409: Deterministic ordering test
- Prior test: "Loading set BEFORE invoke" used observational order capture.
  State was subscribed AFTER bootOrchestrator started, relying on timing.
- New test: uses synchronization-primitive gate (Promise). bootOrchestrator is
  started with a gate-blocked invokeAppStartup. The store is read synchronously
  BEFORE the gate is released. If 'Loading' is not set before await, this assertion
  fails definitively (not spuriously).
- Test file: src/lib/ui/app-shell/__tests__/app-shell-state.test.ts
  Test name: "FIND-409: Loading is set BEFORE invoke — contractual (synchronization-primitive gate)"

## FIND-410: DOM-mount constraint
- @testing-library/svelte v5.3.1 installed successfully.
- bun:test 1.3.11 has no DOM environment (document === undefined confirmed).
- @testing-library/svelte requires vitest peer dependency and a DOM environment.
- Two tests added:
  1. "FIND-410: DOM environment not available in bun:test 1.3.11" — confirms
     constraint (passes when domUnavailable === true).
  2. "FIND-410: @testing-library/svelte is installed (structural check)" —
     imports @testing-library/svelte/pure (avoids auto-setup hook conflict)
     and verifies render/screen are available. Structural prerequisite confirmed.
- vitest-bridge instruction documented inline in test file.

